Document: class_skeletonprofilehumanoid  
Path: godot/classes/class_skeletonprofilehumanoid.rst  
Summary: A read-only SkeletonProfile preset optimized for humanoid character skeletons, defining 56 bones grouped into body, face, and hands.  

A SkeletonProfileHumanoid is a specialized preset for humanoid skeletons, with all parameters locked to ensure consistency across projects. It organizes 56 bones into four groups: "Body," "Face," "LeftHand," and "RightHand." The hierarchical structure begins at the Root, branching into Hips, Spine, and Chest. The Hips connect to LeftUpperLeg and RightUpperLeg, each leading to lower legs, feet, and toes. The Spine extends through Chest and UpperChest, connecting to the Neck and Head. The Head contains Jaw, LeftEye, and RightEye. Shoulders branch into arms, with each arm containing UpperArm, LowerArm, and Hand. Each hand has distinct finger bones: ThumbMetacarpal, ThumbProximal, ThumbDistal, and similarly structured Index, Middle, Ring, and Little fingers. The hierarchy ensures standardized bone placement for humanoid animations and rigging.
